  "favicon": "https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fill,h_80,q_80,w_80/v4sckews2f3bzf0ztbkf.png",
  "text": "Screenshot: Naughty Dog, Marvel / Kotaku, The Game Awards / Kotaku, 2K Games / X / mnm345x / Kotaku, Naughty Dog / Sony / Kotaku, Image: Activision, FromSoftware / Bandai Namco, Game Awards / Sony / Square Enix / PlayStack / Kotaku, Arrowhead Studios, Epic Games / LegoThe 2024 Game Awards were held this past Thursday and unsurprisingly, the reveals that occurred at Geoff Keighley’s big show dwarfed most other happenings in the world of games this week. In addition to our exhaustive breakdown of everything revealed at this year’s event, we’ve got closer looks at The Witcher 4, Mafia: The Old Country, Intergalactic: The Heretic Prophet, and more. Screenshot: Naughty DogIt’s that time of year when the video game industry gathers in Los Angeles to hear Geoff Keighley talk about what a good year it was, whether that’s actually true or not. But as we reflect on the last 12 months, we also get several trailers for games that are coming out in the future. If you weren’t able to catch the show and just want the highlights of what world premieres were there, here’s a rundown of every trailer and announcement made during The Game Awards 2024. - Kenneth Shepard Read MoreScreenshot: Marvel / KotakuMarvel Rivals launched last week, and as fans are flocking to the game in droves, they’re also figuring out who their favorite and least favorite characters are on the hero shooter’s roster. Right now, the game feels like it’s in the pre-patch state of just being a real chaotic shooter that hasn’t yet been sanded down by months of balance patches. Currently, few characters are as chaotic as Jeff the Land Shark, the strategist hero who is, at a glance, just a silly little guy. However, as Marvel Rivals players have learned, this happy dude is actually one of the biggest menaces in the game, and god, I hope NetEase keeps him like this forever. - Kenneth Shepard Read MoreImage: ActivisionBlack Ops 6, the latest entry in the Call of Duty series, contains some really bizarre and wacky cosmetics. And while some players hate them, it doesn’t seem like the developers behind the game are going to stop making them any time soon. - Zack Zwiezen Read MoreScreenshot: The Game Awards / KotakuWe finally have our first taste of The Witcher 4 and it looks stunning in a new cinematic trailer that aired at The Game Awards 2024. The cinematic tease showed monster hunter Ciri stepping into mentor Geralt of Rivia’s shoes to take on a gnarly-looking beast in proper witcher fashion. - Ethan Gach Read MoreImage: FromSoftware / Bandai NamcoFromSoftware isn’t done with Elden Ring yet. The hit open-world RPG that just got a GOTY-nominated expansion is coming back with a completely new spin-off in 2025. It’s called Elden Ring: Nightreign and it’s a co-op action adventure that looks as excellent as the game it’s based on. - Ethan Gach Read MoreImage: Game Awards / Sony / Square Enix / PlayStack / KotakuAnd so, another Game Awards is done. Geoff Keighley’s annual trailer-a-thon once again included some game awards shoved in between all the ads and teasers and more ads. If you want to know who won what (and who lost), we’ve got you covered. - Zack Zwiezen Read MoreScreenshot: 2K Games / X / mnm345x / KotakuThe fourth entry in 2K’s gangster series isn’t far away. A new leaked ad for Mafia: The Old Country ahead of The Game Awards 2024 reveals a summer 2025 release window and our first real look at the upcoming prequel. - Ethan Gach Read MoreImage: Arrowhead StudiosHelldivers 2 fans have been waiting patiently (and not so patiently) for the alien horde shooter to add a new enemy faction, and Arrowhead Studios is finally doing just that. The Illuminate are now live in the game following a surprise free update called Omens of Tyranny, and it adds a ton more than just the series’ infamous blue aquatic aliens. - Ethan Gach Read MoreScreenshot: Naughty Dog / Sony / KotakuThe Game Awards ended with a big finale, a new trailer revealing Naughty Dog’s next game. It’s called Intergalactic: The Heretic Prophet and it looks really, really cool and stylish, mixing lo-fi tech and sci-fi bounty hunters. - Zack Zwiezen Read MoreImage: Epic Games / LegoLater this week, Epic will release Lego Brick Life, a GTA-inspired roleplaying game that will be playable in Fortnite. Brick Life will let you and up to 20+ other players hang out, earn money, buy a home, and party together. - Zack Zwiezen Read More",
